This paper deals with matching mechanisms in a many-to-many market with preferences and ties, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also introduces a mechanism that uses network flows, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the issue of strategic manipulation, which is a topic often studied in social choice theory (cs.SI).
